      {
        "id": 80554,
        "name": "Peter C.",
        "username": "Peter_C",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/peter_c/{size}/76875_2.png",
        "created_at": "2009-07-07T17:48:31.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A stunner of a wine for under $20.</p>\n<p>There\u2019s something for everybody here, minerality/sous bois/florals/bright red fruits/acidity/some tannin - there\u2019s even a little gaminess to be discovered.</p>\n<p>The wine is substantial and not wimpy, in fact, it took a good 3 hours to show it\u2019s true colors, fighting through the ample structure.</p>\n<p>Despite what at first appears to be near impenetrable, it is astonishingly airy, precise and long in the mouth.  A treat to drink, and bottles like this make me revisit why I dont own more cru bojo.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-01T10:23:33.919Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
