      {
        "id": 80568,
        "name": "Scott Smith",
        "username": "Scott_Smith",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/8797f3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2009-07-07T18:05:52.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I enjoyed Burgaud\u2019s Regnie Vallieres 07 a couple weeks ago - my first taste of this producer. It was nice in a racy style - it was probably too chilled to get the most out of it though.</p>\n<p>The more cru beaujolais I taste, the more I gravitate to Morgon. Foillard\u2019s 06 Cote du Py this past weekend was terrific with delicious, focused cherry and cranberry flavors and plenty of structure.</p>",
        "post_number": 2,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-01T10:23:34.575Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
